    <item>
      <title>Blog: Setting up cam traps on the Lez river</title>
      <link>/en/blog/2023/01/12/setting-up-cam-traps-on-the-lez-river/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 12 Jan 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/en/blog/2023/01/12/setting-up-cam-traps-on-the-lez-river/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        
        <![CDATA[<img src="/en/blog/2023/01/12/setting-up-cam-traps-on-the-lez-river/featured-trap-get_hufd2c9877c3614a503618f558eff7ffe2_3928875_640x0_resize_q75_catmullrom.jpeg" width="640" height="480"/>]]>
        
        &lt;p&gt;On January 10th and 12th, we installed about 20 camera traps to capture the fauna of the Lez, hoping that the otter will let itself be photographed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;
  &lt;img src=&#34;traps.png&#34;&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The otter is present on the stream since we found spraints, the technical term for otter scats, tracks, as well as remains of meal (a crayfish).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;
  &lt;img src=&#34;traces.png&#34;&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

      </description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Blog: The OtterConnect project is launched!</title>
      <link>/en/blog/2023/01/01/the-otterconnect-project-is-launched/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 01 Jan 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/en/blog/2023/01/01/the-otterconnect-project-is-launched/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        
        <![CDATA[<img src="/en/blog/2023/01/01/the-otterconnect-project-is-launched/featured-logo-get_hu64728421fa4ddb042661b73822ee517a_52756_640x0_resize_catmullrom_3.png" width="640" height="628"/>]]>
        
        &lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;OtterConnect&lt;/code&gt; project is launched with the support of &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.montpellier.fr/&#34;&gt;Montpellier city&lt;/a&gt;, de  &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.montpellier3m.fr/&#34;&gt;Montpellier Méditerranée Métropole&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.umontpellier.fr/&#34;&gt;University of Montpellier&lt;/a&gt; via &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.labex-cemeb.org/&#34;&gt;Labex Cemeb&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&#34;center&#34;&gt;
  &lt;img width=&#34;460&#34; height=&#34;300&#34; src=&#34;logo-otterconnect.png&#34; alt=&#34;OtterConnect project logo. Olivier Gimenez / CC-BY-CA&#34;&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the &lt;code&gt;OtterConnect&lt;/code&gt; project, we study connectivity on rivers in the Montpellier area (Hérault, Lez, Vidourle, Orb/Libron, Or), with the European otter (&lt;em&gt;Lutra lutra&lt;/em&gt;) as a case study, and as an indicator of green and blue infrastructures. We use non-invasive monitoring methods such as environmental DNA, camera trapping, spraint collection, statistical modeling and social sciences.&lt;/p&gt;

      </description>
    </item>
    
